#!/bin/bash


proc=$RANDOM
touch /tmp/$proc
proc=/tmp/$proc
ps |grep joel>$proc
p='killprocess️️️️🔌:'
#k=$(free -h|awk '/^Mem:/ {print $3"("$2")"}')
#p=$k$p
p=$p
process=$(ps auxch --sort -%cpu,-%mem|awk  '{print $3 "\t"$4"\t"$2"\t"$11}'|rofi -dmenu -width 30 -yoffset -210 -xoffset 485 -p "$p"|awk '{print $3}') && pname=$(ps cax|egrep -w -m1 $process|awk '{print $5}')&& sudo kill "$process" && notify-send  "$pname was killed !🔪"
#nice
